{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014kAvuMS8xFtQUkM9ytZJLw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n     2→\n     3→/// Fixed tier entry amounts in lamports.\n     4→/// Index 0 = Iron, 1 = Bronze, 2 = Silver, 3 = Gold, 4 = Platinum, 5 = Diamond\n     5→pub const TIER_AMOUNTS: [u64; 6] = [\n     6→    5_000_000,       // 0.005 SOL — Iron\n     7→    10_000_000,      // 0.01  SOL — Bronze\n     8→    100_000_000,     // 0.1   SOL — Silver\n     9→    250_000_000,     // 0.25  SOL — Gold\n    10→    500_000_000,     // 0.5   SOL — Platinum\n    11→    1_000_000_000,   // 1.0   SOL — Diamond\n    12→];\n    13→\n    14→pub const TIER_COUNT: usize = TIER_AMOUNTS.len();\n    15→\n    16→/// Returns the entry amount for the given tier index, or an error if out of range.\n    17→pub fn get_tier_amount(tier: u8) -> Result<u64> {\n    18→    TIER_AMOUNTS\n    19→        .get(tier as usize)\n    20→        .copied()\n    21→        .ok_or_else(|| error!(TierError::InvalidTier))\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→#[error_code]\n    25→pub enum TierError {\n    26→    #[msg(\"Invalid tier index\")]\n    27→    InvalidTier,\n    28→}\n    29→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DfD9Rj3j1sZomWEvmsDpHp","session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"6dec6f76-7a07-4a33-a687-717e4c1b57b3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Fbij5mmWtBHgJEXS5c6VB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read the full lordofrngs test file. Here's what I found:\n\n## Test Structure & Patterns\n\nThe file uses **bankrun** for Solana program testing with the following patterns:\n\n### Key Components:\n\n1. **Setup (Lines 19-22)**: Loads IDL from compiled target directory and extracts PROGRAM_ID\n2. **PDA Helper (Lines 27-33)**: `getConfigPda()` derives the config account using `PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync()`\n3. **Test Context Factory (Lines 38-75)**:\n   - `fundedAccountData()` - creates mock account with SOL balance\n   - `createTestContext()` - initializes bankrun context, creates treasury keypair, sets up provider and program instance\n   - Returns an interface with: `context`, `creator` (wallet), `treasury` (keypair), `creatorProgram`, `configPda`\n\n4. **Instruction Helper (Lines 80-89)**: `initConfig()` - wraps the initialize_config RPC call\n5. **Test Suite (Lines 94-111)**: Single test verifying config creation\n\n### Test Pattern Template:\n```typescript\nit(\"description\", async () => {\n  const t = await createTestContext();\n  \n  // Call instruction helper\n  await initConfig(t);\n  \n  // Fetch account and verify\n  const config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(t.configPda);\n  \n  // Assert with chai expect()\n  expect(config.field).to.equal(expectedValue);\n});\n```\n\n## Key Observations for `create_round`:\n\n1. **PDA derivation needed** - You'll need a helper like `getRoundPda()` to derive the round account PDA\n2. **Instruction helper pattern** - Create an `initRound()` or `createRound()` helper function similar to `initConfig()`\n3. **Account verification** - Use `.fetch()` on the account type to verify state post-instruction\n4. **Chai assertions** - Use `expect().to.equal()` for primitives, `.to.deep.equal()` for arrays/objects\n5. **Context reuse** - The `TestContext` interface provides everything needed; no special setup required per test\n\nThe testing approach is straightforward and maintainable—add your `create_round` test following the same structure within the describe block or a new nested describe(\"create_round\") block."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a61db5f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 28008\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 7969</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"968997f0-21bd-496f-b446-b34cf3081fbc","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of the lordofrngs test file at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts`. I need to understand the existing test patterns and helpers to add the create_round test.","agentId":"a61db5f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read the full lordofrngs test file. Here's what I found:\n\n## Test Structure & Patterns\n\nThe file uses **bankrun** for Solana program testing with the following patterns:\n\n### Key Components:\n\n1. **Setup (Lines 19-22)**: Loads IDL from compiled target directory and extracts PROGRAM_ID\n2. **PDA Helper (Lines 27-33)**: `getConfigPda()` derives the config account using `PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync()`\n3. **Test Context Factory (Lines 38-75)**:\n   - `fundedAccountData()` - creates mock account with SOL balance\n   - `createTestContext()` - initializes bankrun context, creates treasury keypair, sets up provider and program instance\n   - Returns an interface with: `context`, `creator` (wallet), `treasury` (keypair), `creatorProgram`, `configPda`\n\n4. **Instruction Helper (Lines 80-89)**: `initConfig()` - wraps the initialize_config RPC call\n5. **Test Suite (Lines 94-111)**: Single test verifying config creation\n\n### Test Pattern Template:\n```typescript\nit(\"description\", async () => {\n  const t = await createTestContext();\n  \n  // Call instruction helper\n  await initConfig(t);\n  \n  // Fetch account and verify\n  const config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(t.configPda);\n  \n  // Assert with chai expect()\n  expect(config.field).to.equal(expectedValue);\n});\n```\n\n## Key Observations for `create_round`:\n\n1. **PDA derivation needed** - You'll need a helper like `getRoundPda()` to derive the round account PDA\n2. **Instruction helper pattern** - Create an `initRound()` or `createRound()` helper function similar to `initConfig()`\n3. **Account verification** - Use `.fetch()` on the account type to verify state post-instruction\n4. **Chai assertions** - Use `expect().to.equal()` for primitives, `.to.deep.equal()` for arrays/objects\n5. **Context reuse** - The `TestContext` interface provides everything needed; no special setup required per test\n\nThe testing approach is straightforward and maintainable—add your `create_round` test following the same structure within the describe block or a new nested describe(\"create_round\") block."}],"totalDurationMs":7969,"totalTokens":28008,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3435,"cache_read_input_tokens":23994,"output_tokens":574,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3435,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DfD9Rj3j1sZomWEvmsDpHp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have the full contents of all three files. Here's a complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Program - Game Creation Pattern\n\n### 1. **CreateMatch Instruction** (`create_match.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/create_match.rs`\n\nThis instruction is named `CreateMatch` (not `create_game`) and follows this pattern:\n\n**Account Structure:**\n- `creator` (Signer, Mutable): The player creating the match; must fund the escrow\n- `coinflip_match` (Init): A match PDA with seeds `[b\"match\", creator.key()]` — enforces one active match per creator\n- `config` (Read-only): Global config PDA for pause checking\n- `system_program`: For account creation\n\n**Handler Signature:**\n```rust\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<CreateMatch>, tier: u8, side: u8) -> Result<()>\n```\n\n**Logic Flow:**\n1. Check if the game is paused (reject new matches if paused)\n2. Validate the side (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails) via `is_valid_side()`\n3. Look up entry amount from tier via `get_tier_amount(tier)`\n4. Transfer lamports from creator to match PDA (escrow)\n5. Initialize match state with:\n   - Creator and opponent (Pubkey::default initially)\n   - Tier and entry amount\n   - Creator's chosen side\n   - Phase: `RoundPhase::Waiting`\n   - Default values for result, winner, locked_at, resolve_deadline, vrf_request_key\n   - Timestamp: `created_at = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp`\n   - Bump seed\n\n---\n\n### 2. **State Definitions** (`state.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n**CoinflipConfig** (PDA: `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`):\n- `authority`: Admin pubkey\n- `treasury`: Fee destination wallet\n- `paused`: Boolean flag to pause match creation\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n**CoinflipMatch** (PDA: `[b\"match\", creator.key()]`):\n- `creator`: Creator's pubkey\n- `opponent`: Opponent's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until joined)\n- `tier`: Tier index (0-5)\n- `entry_amount`: Lamports (derived from tier)\n- `creator_side`: Side chosen (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails)\n- `phase`: Current `RoundPhase` (Waiting, Locked, Settled, etc.)\n- `result`: Winning side (0 or 1, only valid when settled)\n- `winner`: Winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled)\n- `claimed`: Whether payout has been claimed\n- `created_at`: Unix timestamp at creation\n- `locked_at`: Unix timestamp when match entered Locked phase (0 if still Waiting)\n- `resolve_deadline`: Deadline for VRF resolution (after this, timeout refund available)\n- `vrf_request_key`: Address of the Orao randomness PDA for VRF lookup at claim time\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n**MatchSettled Event:**\n- Emitted during `claim_payout`\n- Contains: creator, opponent, winner, randomness [u8; 32], payout_amount, fee_amount, vrf_request_key\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Tier System** (`tiers.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/tiers.rs`\n\n**Fixed Tier Amounts** (6 tiers in lamports):\n```\nIndex 0: Iron     = 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL)\nIndex 1: Bronze   = 10,000,000 lamports (0.01 SOL)\nIndex 2: Silver   = 100,000,000 lamports (0.1 SOL)\nIndex 3: Gold     = 250,000,000 lamports (0.25 SOL)\nIndex 4: Platinum = 500,000,000 lamports (0.5 SOL)\nIndex 5: Diamond  = 1,000,000,000 lamports (1.0 SOL)\n```\n\n**Function:**\n```rust\npub fn get_tier_amount(tier: u8) -> Result<u64>\n```\nReturns the entry amount for a given tier index, or errors with `TierError::InvalidTier` if out of range.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns\n\n1. **Match PDA is seeded by creator's pubkey** — enforces one active match per creator\n2. **Tier → Amount lookup** happens at instruction time via the shared `get_tier_amount()` function\n3. **Escrow pattern**: Lamports are transferred to the match PDA at creation (held in account's balance)\n4. **State initialization**: Most fields are zeroed/defaulted; critical fields like phase, side, and timestamp are set\n5. **VRF request key**: Populated later during settlement flow, not at creation"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aff296b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31023\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 18171</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"f1fb5835-1406-4c6c-a56d-0a069b9a5793","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the coinflip program's create_game/game creation pattern. Find and read the following:\n\n1. The coinflip `create_game` instruction (search in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/` for the create_game instruction)\n2. The coinflip state definitions (look at state.rs or state/mod.rs in the coinflip program)\n3. The shared crate's tier-related functions/constants — look at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/` for tiers\n\nReturn the FULL contents of these files.","agentId":"aff296b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have the full contents of all three files. Here's a complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Program - Game Creation Pattern\n\n### 1. **CreateMatch Instruction** (`create_match.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/create_match.rs`\n\nThis instruction is named `CreateMatch` (not `create_game`) and follows this pattern:\n\n**Account Structure:**\n- `creator` (Signer, Mutable): The player creating the match; must fund the escrow\n- `coinflip_match` (Init): A match PDA with seeds `[b\"match\", creator.key()]` — enforces one active match per creator\n- `config` (Read-only): Global config PDA for pause checking\n- `system_program`: For account creation\n\n**Handler Signature:**\n```rust\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<CreateMatch>, tier: u8, side: u8) -> Result<()>\n```\n\n**Logic Flow:**\n1. Check if the game is paused (reject new matches if paused)\n2. Validate the side (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails) via `is_valid_side()`\n3. Look up entry amount from tier via `get_tier_amount(tier)`\n4. Transfer lamports from creator to match PDA (escrow)\n5. Initialize match state with:\n   - Creator and opponent (Pubkey::default initially)\n   - Tier and entry amount\n   - Creator's chosen side\n   - Phase: `RoundPhase::Waiting`\n   - Default values for result, winner, locked_at, resolve_deadline, vrf_request_key\n   - Timestamp: `created_at = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp`\n   - Bump seed\n\n---\n\n### 2. **State Definitions** (`state.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n**CoinflipConfig** (PDA: `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`):\n- `authority`: Admin pubkey\n- `treasury`: Fee destination wallet\n- `paused`: Boolean flag to pause match creation\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n**CoinflipMatch** (PDA: `[b\"match\", creator.key()]`):\n- `creator`: Creator's pubkey\n- `opponent`: Opponent's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until joined)\n- `tier`: Tier index (0-5)\n- `entry_amount`: Lamports (derived from tier)\n- `creator_side`: Side chosen (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails)\n- `phase`: Current `RoundPhase` (Waiting, Locked, Settled, etc.)\n- `result`: Winning side (0 or 1, only valid when settled)\n- `winner`: Winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled)\n- `claimed`: Whether payout has been claimed\n- `created_at`: Unix timestamp at creation\n- `locked_at`: Unix timestamp when match entered Locked phase (0 if still Waiting)\n- `resolve_deadline`: Deadline for VRF resolution (after this, timeout refund available)\n- `vrf_request_key`: Address of the Orao randomness PDA for VRF lookup at claim time\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n**MatchSettled Event:**\n- Emitted during `claim_payout`\n- Contains: creator, opponent, winner, randomness [u8; 32], payout_amount, fee_amount, vrf_request_key\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Tier System** (`tiers.rs`)\n**Full file path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/tiers.rs`\n\n**Fixed Tier Amounts** (6 tiers in lamports):\n```\nIndex 0: Iron     = 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL)\nIndex 1: Bronze   = 10,000,000 lamports (0.01 SOL)\nIndex 2: Silver   = 100,000,000 lamports (0.1 SOL)\nIndex 3: Gold     = 250,000,000 lamports (0.25 SOL)\nIndex 4: Platinum = 500,000,000 lamports (0.5 SOL)\nIndex 5: Diamond  = 1,000,000,000 lamports (1.0 SOL)\n```\n\n**Function:**\n```rust\npub fn get_tier_amount(tier: u8) -> Result<u64>\n```\nReturns the entry amount for a given tier index, or errors with `TierError::InvalidTier` if out of range.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns\n\n1. **Match PDA is seeded by creator's pubkey** — enforces one active match per creator\n2. **Tier → Amount lookup** happens at instruction time via the shared `get_tier_amount()` function\n3. **Escrow pattern**: Lamports are transferred to the match PDA at creation (held in account's balance)\n4. **State initialization**: Most fields are zeroed/defaulted; critical fields like phase, side, and timestamp are set\n5. **VRF request key**: Populated later during settlement flow, not at creation"}],"totalDurationMs":18171,"totalTokens":31023,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4745,"cache_read_input_tokens":24970,"output_tokens":1301,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4745,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
