{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01W7NvdFhpokmW9Tow7PksPM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error persists with `&[tier]` — Anchor is interpreting the array dimensions differently. The issue is that Anchor's `init` macro tries to match seed types statically. The `to_le_bytes()` of a `u64` returns `[u8; 8]`, and `&[tier]` returns `[u8; 1]`, but Anchor's macro processing is expanding `&[tier]` into something unexpected. Let me check the coinflip pattern again — the coinflip uses `creator.key().as_ref()` which returns `&[u8]` (a slice). Let me try using slice references for the seeds."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3006,"cache_read_input_tokens":66681,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3006},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"e7158f2e-4b21-4da8-b29d-aa723d514770"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01W7NvdFhpokmW9Tow7PksPM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NgD3k3Wi3iXxudT4D9gjus","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/create_round.rs","content":"use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_to_pda;\nuse rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase;\nuse rng_shared::pause::check_not_paused;\nuse rng_shared::tiers::get_tier_amount;\n\nuse crate::error::LordError;\nuse crate::state::{JackpotRound, LordConfig, PlayerEntry};\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\n#[instruction(tier: u8, round_number: u64)]\npub struct CreateRound<'info> {\n    /// The player creating the round. Signs and pays rent + first entry.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// Global config PDA (mutable — we increment the round counter).\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"lord_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, LordConfig>,\n\n    /// The round PDA. Seeds: [b\"jackpot_round\", tier (1 byte), round_number (8 bytes LE)]\n    #[account(\n        init,\n        payer = creator,\n        space = 8 + JackpotRound::INIT_SPACE,\n        seeds = [\n            b\"jackpot_round\",\n            tier.to_le_bytes().as_ref(),\n            round_number.to_le_bytes().as_ref(),\n        ],\n        bump,\n    )]\n    pub round: Account<'info, JackpotRound>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<CreateRound>, tier: u8, round_number: u64, num_entries: u32) -> Result<()> {\n    // Pause check\n    check_not_paused(false, ctx.accounts.config.paused)?;\n\n    // Validate tier\n    let entry_amount = get_tier_amount(tier).map_err(|_| LordError::InvalidTier)?;\n\n    // Must buy at least one entry\n    require!(num_entries > 0, LordError::ZeroEntries);\n\n    // Validate round_number matches current counter for this tier\n    let expected_round = ctx.accounts.config.round_counters[tier as usize];\n    require!(round_number == expected_round, LordError::InvalidPhase);\n\n    // Total cost = entry_amount × num_entries\n    let total_cost = entry_amount\n        .checked_mul(num_entries as u64)\n        .ok_or(LordError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n\n    // Transfer lamports to round PDA (escrow)\n    transfer_lamports_to_pda(\n        &ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.round.to_account_info(),\n        total_cost,\n        &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n    )?;\n\n    let now = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n\n    // Increment the round counter for this tier\n    ctx.accounts.config.round_counters[tier as usize] = round_number\n        .checked_add(1)\n        .ok_or(LordError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n\n    // Initialize round state\n    let round = &mut ctx.accounts.round;\n    round.tier = tier;\n    round.round_number = round_number;\n    round.entry_amount = entry_amount;\n    round.phase = RoundPhase::Waiting;\n    round.players = vec![PlayerEntry {\n        player: ctx.accounts.creator.key(),\n        entries: num_entries,\n    }];\n    round.total_entries = num_entries;\n    round.created_at = now;\n    round.countdown_ends_at = 0;\n    round.locked_at = 0;\n    round.resolve_deadline = 0;\n    round.vrf_request_key = Pubkey::default();\n    round.winning_slot = 0;\n    round.winner = Pubkey::default();\n    round.claimed = false;\n    round.creator = ctx.accounts.creator.key();\n    round.bump = ctx.bumps.round;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3006,"cache_read_input_tokens":66681,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3006},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"50e288cf-c190-4909-bdb5-e9fbc8ac8e28"}
