entMatchPda = getMatchPda(t.opponent.publicKey);\n   834→      try {\n   835→        await t.opponentProgram.methods\n   836→          .cancelMatch()\n   837→          .accounts({\n   838→            creator: t.opponent.publicKey,\n   839→            coinflipMatch: opponentMatchPda,\n   840→            systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   841→          })\n   842→          .rpc();\n   843→        expect.fail(\"Expected error\");\n   844→      } catch (err) {\n   845→        // PDA doesn't exist → AccountNotInitialized\n   846→        expect(err).to.exist;\n   847→      }\n   848→    });\n   849→  });\n   850→\n   851→  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   852→  // timeout_cancel\n   853→  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   854→  describe(\"timeout_cancel\", () => {\n   855→    it(\"permissionless refund after deadline when VRF unfulfilled\", async () => {\n   856→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   857→      await initConfig(t);\n   858→      await createMatch(t);\n   859→      await joinMatch(t);\n   860→      // Randomness stays unfulfilled (all zeros)\n   861→\n   862→      await warpPastDeadline(t);\n   863→\n   864→      const creatorBefore = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   865→      const opponentBefore = await getBalance(t, t.opponent.publicKey);\n   866→\n   867→      // Third party triggers timeout (permissionless)\n   868→      const thirdParty = Keypair.generate();\n   869→      t.context.setAccount(thirdParty.publicKey, fundedAccountData());\n   870→      const thirdProvider = new BankrunProvider(\n   871→        t.context,\n   872→        new Wallet(thirdParty)\n   873→      );\n   874→      const thirdProgram = new Program<Coinflip>(IDL, thirdProvider);\n   875→\n   876→      await timeoutCancel(t, thirdProgram, thirdParty.publicKey);\n   877→\n   878→      const creatorAfter = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   879→      const opponentAfter = await getBalance(t, t.opponent.publicKey);\n   880→\n   881→      // Both players refunded entry amounts\n   882→      // Creator also gets rent refund from closed PDA\n   883→      expect(creatorAfter - creatorBefore).to.be.greaterThanOrEqual(\n   884→        TIER_IRON_AMOUNT\n   885→      );\n   886→      expect(opponentAfter - opponentBefore).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\n   887→\n   888→      const matchAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(t.matchPda);\n   889→      expect(matchAccount).to.be.null;\n   890→    });\n   891→\n   892→    it(\"rejects timeout before deadline\", async () => {\n   893→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   894→      await initConfig(t);\n   895→      await createMatch(t);\n   896→      await joinMatch(t);\n   897→      // Don't warp clock\n   898→\n   899→      try {\n   900→        await timeoutCancel(t, t.creatorProgram, t.creator);\n   901→        expect.fail(\"Expected LockTimeoutNotElapsed error\");\n   902→      } catch (err) {\n   903→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\n   904→          \"LockTimeoutNotElapsed\"\n   905→        );\n   906→      }\n   907→    });\n   908→\n   909→    it(\"rejects timeout when VRF IS fulfilled — must claim instead\", async () => {\n   910→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   911→      await initConfig(t);\n   912→      await createMatch(t);\n   913→      await joinMatch(t);\n   914→\n   915→      // Set fulfilled randomness\n   916→      setMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_HEADS);\n   917→      await warpPastDeadline(t);\n   918→\n   919→      try {\n   920→        await timeoutCancel(t, t.creatorProgram, t.creator);\n   921→        expect.fail(\"Expected error — VRF fulfilled, must claim\");\n   922→      } catch (err) {\n   923→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\n   924→          \"InvalidPhase\"\n   925→        );\n   926→      }\n   927→    });\n   928→  });\n   929→\n   930→  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   931→  // full lifecycle\n   932→  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   933→  describe(\"full lifecycle\", () => {\n   934→    it(\"create → join → claim(HEADS) → PDA closed\", async () => {\n   935→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   936→      await initConfig(t);\n   937→      await setupPlatform(t);\n   938→\n   939→      await createMatch(t, TIER_IRON, SIDE_HEADS);\n   940→      let m = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(t.matchPda);\n   941→      expect(JSON.stringify(m.phase)).to.equal(\n   942→        JSON.stringify({ waiting: {} })\n   943→      );\n   944→\n   945→      await joinMatch(t);\n   946→      m = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(t.matchPda);\n   947→      expect(JSON.stringify(m.phase)).to.equal(\n   948→        JSON.stringify({ locked: {} })\n   949→      );\n   950→\n   951→      setMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_HEADS);\n   952→\n   953→      const pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2;\n   954→      const fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   955→      const treasuryBefore = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   956→\n   957→      await claimPayout(t, t.creatorProgram, t.creator);\n   958→\n   959→      const treasuryAfter = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   960→      expect(treasuryAfter - treasuryBefore).to.equal(fee);\n   961→\n   962→      const closed = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(t.matchPda);\n   963→      expect(closed).to.be.null;\n   964→    });\n   965→\n   966→    it(\"create → cancel → create again\", async () => {\n   967→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   968→      await initConfig(t);\n   969→\n   970→      await createMatch(t, TIER_IRON, SIDE_HEADS);\n   971→      await cancelMatch(t);\n   972→\n   973→      const closed = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(t.matchPda);\n   974→      expect(closed).to.be.null;\n   975→\n   976→      // Create again (same PDA slot is free)\n   977→      await createMatch(t, TIER_IRON, SIDE_TAILS);\n   978→      const m = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(t.matchPda);\n   979→      expect(m.creatorSide).to.equal(SIDE_TAILS);\n   980→      expect(JSON.stringify(m.phase)).to.equal(\n   981→        JSON.stringify({ waiting: {} })\n   982→      );\n   983→    });\n   984→\n   985→    it(\"create → join → timeout (VRF unfulfilled) → both refunded\", async () => {\n   986→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   987→      await initConfig(t);\n   988→\n   989→      await createMatch(t, TIER_IRON, SIDE_HEADS);\n   990→      await joinMatch(t);\n   991→\n   992→      await warpPastDeadline(t);\n   993→\n   994→      const creatorBefore = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   995→      const opponentBefore = await getBalance(t, t.opponent.publicKey);\n   996→\n   997→      await timeoutCancel(t, t.opponentProgram, t.opponent.publicKey);\n   998→\n   999→      const creatorAfter = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n  1000→      const opponentAfter = await getBalance(t, t.opponent.publicKey);\n  1001→\n  1002→      expect(creatorAfter - creatorBefore).to.be.greaterThanOrEqual(\n  1003→        TIER_IRON_AMOUNT\n  1004→      );\n  1005→      expect(opponentAfter - opponentBefore).to.be.greaterThanOrEqual(\n  1006→        TIER_IRON_AMOUNT - 5000\n  1007→      ); // minus tx fee\n  1008→    });\n  1009→  });\n  1010→});\n  1011→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012nuUxQe35SiGtAhk6hRM52","session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"f579c060-f39b-4329-929d-79d9c3e75b43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012nuUxQe35SiGtAhk6hRM52","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read the complete test file. Here are the key sections addressing your four questions:\n\n## 1. PDA Helpers Structure\n\nThe file uses a clean, straightforward approach for PDAs (lines 60-90):\n\n```typescript\nfunction getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getPlayerProfilePda(wallet: PublicKey): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), wallet.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: Each PDA uses a string seed buffer (e.g., `\"match\"`) + optional wallet/account buffers, seeded against the program ID.\n\n## 2. Creating Matches & Verifying Account Data\n\nThe test on line 379 (\"creates match in Waiting phase with correct escrow\") shows the pattern:\n\n```typescript\nasync function createMatch(\n  t: TestContext,\n  tier = TIER_IRON,\n  side = SIDE_HEADS\n) {\n  await t.creatorProgram.methods\n    .createMatch(tier, side)\n    .accounts({\n      creator: t.creator,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n\n// Then fetch and verify:\nconst m = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(t.matchPda);\nexpect(m.creator.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\nexpect(m.opponent.toBase58()).to.equal(PublicKey.default.toBase58());\nexpect(m.tier).to.equal(TIER_IRON);\nexpect(m.entryAmount.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\nexpect(m.creatorSide).to.equal(SIDE_HEADS);\nexpect(JSON.stringify(m.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ waiting: {} }));\nexpect(m.claimed).to.equal(false);\nexpect(m.createdAt.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(0);\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: \n- Call the instruction method with parameters\n- Pass all required accounts from the PDA helpers\n- Fetch the account using Anchor's `.fetch()` \n- Assert all fields match expected values\n- Discriminated unions (like `phase`) are checked via `JSON.stringify()`\n\n## 3. Big Number (BN) Conversion for Tier Amounts\n\nThe tests consistently use `.toNumber()` to convert from BN (lines 388, 406, 743-754):\n\n```typescript\n// Constants defined at top (lines 36-39):\nconst TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL in lamports\n\n// Converting in assertions:\nexpect(m.entryAmount.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\n\n// Payout calculations (lines 564-566):\nconst pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2;\nconst fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\nconst payout = pool - fee;\n\n// Checking profile stats (lines 743-746):\nexpect(cp.totalGames.toNumber()).to.equal(1);\nexpect(cp.wins.toNumber()).to.equal(1);\nexpect(cp.totalWagered.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\nexpect(cp.totalWon.toNumber()).to.equal(payout);\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: On-chain u64 fields come back as BN; use `.toNumber()` for JavaScript arithmetic and assertions.\n\n## 4. Error/Rejection Cases\n\nLines 414-454 show the error testing pattern:\n\n```typescript\nit(\"rejects invalid side\", async () => {\n  const t = await createTestContext();\n  await initConfig(t);\n  try {\n    await t.creatorProgram.methods\n      .createMatch(TIER_IRON, 3)  // Invalid side value\n      .accounts({\n        creator: t.creator,\n        coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n        config: t.configPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .rpc();\n    expect.fail(\"Expected InvalidSide error\");\n  } catch (err) {\n    expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"InvalidSide\");\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Key patterns**:\n- Wrap the instruction call in `try/catch`\n- Use `expect.fail()` if no error is thrown (test fails)\n- Cast error as `AnchorError` and check `.error.errorCode.code` against the expected error name\n- Additional examples: `CannotJoinOwnMatch` (line 507), `RandomnessNotFulfilled` (line 660), `UnauthorizedCaller` (line 721)\n\nAll test errors follow this structure consistently throughout the file (lines 486-547 for join_match errors, 648-724 for claim_payout errors, 811-848 for cancel_match errors)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9493cf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40986\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 15031</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd382642-6e40-406b-af72-e4885c229771","uuid":"b179e75f-bacd-4338-9965-b452153119e2","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the coinflip test file at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`. I need to understand:\n1. How PDA helpers are structured (especially `getMatchPda`)\n2. How they create matches and verify account data\n3. How they handle BN (big number) conversions for tier amounts\n4. How they test error/rejection cases\n\nReturn the relevant sections of the file (especially the first 200 lines, and any test that creates a match).","agentId":"a9493cf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read the complete test file. Here are the key sections addressing your four questions:\n\n## 1. PDA Helpers Structure\n\nThe file uses a clean, straightforward approach for PDAs (lines 60-90):\n\n```typescript\nfunction getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getPlayerProfilePda(wallet: PublicKey): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), wallet.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: Each PDA uses a string seed buffer (e.g., `\"match\"`) + optional wallet/account buffers, seeded against the program ID.\n\n## 2. Creating Matches & Verifying Account Data\n\nThe test on line 379 (\"creates match in Waiting phase with correct escrow\") shows the pattern:\n\n```typescript\nasync function createMatch(\n  t: TestContext,\n  tier = TIER_IRON,\n  side = SIDE_HEADS\n) {\n  await t.creatorProgram.methods\n    .createMatch(tier, side)\n    .accounts({\n      creator: t.creator,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n\n// Then fetch and verify:\nconst m = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(t.matchPda);\nexpect(m.creator.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\nexpect(m.opponent.toBase58()).to.equal(PublicKey.default.toBase58());\nexpect(m.tier).to.equal(TIER_IRON);\nexpect(m.entryAmount.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\nexpect(m.creatorSide).to.equal(SIDE_HEADS);\nexpect(JSON.stringify(m.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ waiting: {} }));\nexpect(m.claimed).to.equal(false);\nexpect(m.createdAt.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(0);\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: \n- Call the instruction method with parameters\n- Pass all required accounts from the PDA helpers\n- Fetch the account using Anchor's `.fetch()` \n- Assert all fields match expected values\n- Discriminated unions (like `phase`) are checked via `JSON.stringify()`\n\n## 3. Big Number (BN) Conversion for Tier Amounts\n\nThe tests consistently use `.toNumber()` to convert from BN (lines 388, 406, 743-754):\n\n```typescript\n// Constants defined at top (lines 36-39):\nconst TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL in lamports\n\n// Converting in assertions:\nexpect(m.entryAmount.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\n\n// Payout calculations (lines 564-566):\nconst pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2;\nconst fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\nconst payout = pool - fee;\n\n// Checking profile stats (lines 743-746):\nexpect(cp.totalGames.toNumber()).to.equal(1);\nexpect(cp.wins.toNumber()).to.equal(1);\nexpect(cp.totalWagered.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\nexpect(cp.totalWon.toNumber()).to.equal(payout);\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: On-chain u64 fields come back as BN; use `.toNumber()` for JavaScript arithmetic and assertions.\n\n## 4. Error/Rejection Cases\n\nLines 414-454 show the error testing pattern:\n\n```typescript\nit(\"rejects invalid side\", async () => {\n  const t = await createTestContext();\n  await initConfig(t);\n  try {\n    await t.creatorProgram.methods\n      .createMatch(TIER_IRON, 3)  // Invalid side value\n      .accounts({\n        creator: t.creator,\n        coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n        config: t.configPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .rpc();\n    expect.fail(\"Expected InvalidSide error\");\n  } catch (err) {\n    expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"InvalidSide\");\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Key patterns**:\n- Wrap the instruction call in `try/catch`\n- Use `expect.fail()` if no error is thrown (test fails)\n- Cast error as `AnchorError` and check `.error.errorCode.code` against the expected error name\n- Additional examples: `CannotJoinOwnMatch` (line 507), `RandomnessNotFulfilled` (line 660), `UnauthorizedCaller` (line 721)\n\nAll test errors follow this structure consistently throughout the file (lines 486-547 for join_match errors, 648-724 for claim_payout errors, 811-848 for cancel_match errors)."}],"totalDurationMs":15031,"totalTokens":40986,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15517,"cache_read_input_tokens":24066,"output_tokens":1398,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests